The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a press gaggle on May 28, 2010, discussing various topics including the President's reaction to the Sestak incident, criticism from supporters like James Carville, and the President's communication with BP CEO Hayward. Gibbs also addressed questions about the top kill procedure to stop the oil spill, the President's meeting with officials from Louisiana, Alabama, and Florida, and the President's plans for the weekend.